Durban - A detainee was shot following a jailbreak at the Umbumbulu Magistrate's Court on the KZN south coast on Tuesday. The jailbreak by three detainees, on Tuesday, at the Umbumbulu Magistrate's Court was however short lived. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said three men overpowered a police officer at the Umbumbulu Magistrate's Court just before 9am. "Two men were apprehended while trying to jump the fence. A third managed to flee the scene in a getaway vehicle that was waiting for him outside the court," he said. Police officers from neighbouring stations responded said Zwane, and began a search for the vehicle. "The vehicle was spotted in uMlazi, in the Bhekithemba area. A shoot-out ensued between the police and the occupants of the car. No injuries were sustained by police officers," he added. The suspect and his accomplice, said Zwane, sustained injuries and were taken to hospital where they are under police guard. A firearm was recovered from one of the men. Daily News